Thirty-nine per cent of Kenyans access the Internet through their mobile phones only, a new report has shown. The report, GlobalWebIndex on Trends 2018, ranked Kenya behind Nigeria in having the highest number of digital consumers whose only access to the Internet is through their mobile handsets. ALSO READ:

